{"event":"pre-tool-use","timestamp":"2026-06-18T13:55:54.212Z","tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"cd /media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-advance-spool-to-next-station-api && git commit -q -m \"feat: advance spool endpoint returns new station, with unit + HTTP tests\n\nEndpoint POST /api/spools/{id}/advance now returns 200 OK with the new\ncurrent station (was 204 No Content); 404/400 unchanged. AdvanceAsync\nreturns AdvanceOutcome carrying the resulting station.\n\nAdds service-level tests (every forward hop, full chain, unknown id,\nadvance-past-Installed leaves state untouched) and HTTP integration tests\nvia WebApplicationFactory. Discovered and documented a latent tie-break\ndefect in Spool.CurrentStation; handed off to the starter-bug playbook.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01NeV3yWZ2eePNzuBft94RrM\" && echo \"committed\" && git log --oneline -3","description":"Commit the work on the task branch"}}
