{"event":"pre-tool-use","timestamp":"2026-06-18T13:56:25.451Z","tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"cd /media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-advance-spool-to-next-station-api && gh pr create --repo fega/full-stack-engineer-ai-code-challenge --base main --head feat/advance-spool-to-next-station-api --title \"feat: advance spool to next station via API (200 + new station, tested)\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\nImplements the acceptance criterion **\"A spool can be advanced to its next station through the API\"** — confirming, hardening, and fully testing the inherited `POST /api/spools/{id}/advance` endpoint.\n\n- `SpoolWorkflowService.AdvanceAsync` now returns `AdvanceOutcome(TransitionResult Result, Station? NewStation)` instead of a bare enum, so callers learn the resulting station. Advance logic is otherwise unchanged (single forward hop via `Station.Next()`, append `StatusEvent`, persist).\n- The endpoint now returns **`200 OK`** with `{ id, currentStation }` on success (was `204 No Content`). `404` (unknown id) and `400` (no next station) are unchanged.\n\n## Contract decision (204 → 200 + body)\n\nChose `200 OK` with the new station so the dashboard/clients see the result of the move without a second `GET /api/spools/{id}` round-trip. No existing client depended on the old `204` (the Vue app does not yet call advance). Refining the forward-only / backward-rejection guard is intentionally left to the sibling task.\n\n## Tests (`dotnet test` → 15 passed)\n\n- **Service-level** (`SpoolWorkflowServiceTests`, fakes + monotonic `FakeClock`): single hop; status event records clock time + actor + preserves history; every forward hop (theory); full chain Detailing→…→Installed; unknown id → `NotFound`; advance at `Installed` rejected with **no** state mutation.\n- **HTTP** (`AdvanceEndpointTests`, `WebApplicationFactory<Program>`, deterministic auto-seed off): `200` + `{ id, currentStation: \"Cut\" }` and observable on re-read; unknown → `404`; past `Installed` → `400`.\n- Added `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing` to the test project.\n\n## Note: latent starter-bug discovered (not fixed here)\n\nWriting the full-chain test surfaced a tie-break defect in `Spool.CurrentStation` — it uses `OrderByDescending(x => x.ChangedAt).First()`, a *stable* sort that returns the earliest-inserted event when timestamps tie. Production `SystemClock` timestamps are monotonic so the shipped endpoint is correct; this PR uses a monotonic test clock rather than masking the feature behind the defect. The fix is handed off to the `find-explain-fix-starter-bug-with-tests` playbook with a concrete repro (documented in the playbook's FOLLOW UP).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -5","description":"Open PR against fork main"}}
