{"event":"pre-tool-use","timestamp":"2026-06-18T13:59:27.136Z","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"/media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-dashboard-wip-per-station/src/stratus-fab-tracker-web/src/views/WipDetailView.vue","content":"<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nimport { computed, onMounted, ref } from 'vue';\nimport { useRoute, useRouter } from 'vue-router';\nimport {\n  api,\n  STATION_ORDER,\n  TERMINAL_STATION,\n  type SpoolSummaryDto,\n  type WipStationCount,\n} from '../api';\n\nconst route = useRoute();\nconst router = useRouter();\n\nconst counts = ref<WipStationCount[]>([]);\nconst spools = ref<SpoolSummaryDto[]>([]);\nconst error = ref('');\nconst loading = ref(true);\n\n// Stations in domain order, falling back to the canonical order if the API is slow.\nconst stations = computed<WipStationCount[]>(() =>\n  counts.value.length\n    ? counts.value\n    : STATION_ORDER.map(station => ({ station, count: 0 }))\n);\n\n// Selected station comes from the URL (?station=) so the view is linkable and\n// the browser back button works. Default to the first station in the chain.\nconst selected = computed(() => {\n  const q = route.query.station;\n  const candidate = Array.isArray(q) ? q[0] : q;\n  return STATION_ORDER.includes(candidate as never)\n    ? (candidate as string)\n    : STATION_ORDER[0];\n});\n\nconst spoolsAtSelected = computed(() =>\n  spools.value.filter(s => s.currentStation === selected.value)\n);\n\nfunction select(station: string) {\n  router.replace({ path: '/wip', query: { station } });\n}\n\nconst dateFmt = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {\n  year: 'numeric',\n  month: 'short',\n  day: 'numeric',\n});\nfunction formatDue(iso: string) {\n  // dueDate is a date-only string (yyyy-MM-dd); parse as local to avoid TZ drift.\n  const [y, m, d] = iso.split('-').map(Number);\n  return dateFmt.format(new Date(y, m - 1, d));\n}\n\nonMounted(async () => {\n  try {\n    const [dash, list] = await Promise.all([api.dashboard(), api.spools()]);\n    counts.value = dash.wipByStation;\n    spools.value = list;\n  } catch {\n    error.value = 'Unable to load WIP detail';\n  } finally {\n    loading.value = false;\n  }\n});\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <p v-if=\"error\" class=\"error\">{{ error }}</p>\n\n  <section v-else>\n    <h2 class=\"section-title\">WIP per station — pick a station to see its spools</h2>\n\n    <div class=\"grid\" style=\"margin-bottom:24px;\">\n      <button\n        v-for=\"s in stations\"\n        :key=\"s.station\"\n        class=\"tile\"\n        :class=\"{ 'is-active': s.station === selected, 'is-terminal': s.station === TERMINAL_STATION }\"\n        type=\"button\"\n        @click=\"select(s.station)\"\n      >\n        <span class=\"tile-count\">{{ s.count }}</span>\n        <span class=\"tile-label\">{{ s.station }}</span>\n        <span v-if=\"s.station === TERMINAL_STATION\" class=\"tile-tag\">Complete</span>\n      </button>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <h3 class=\"section-title\">\n        {{ selected }} · {{ spoolsAtSelected.length }}\n        {{ spoolsAtSelected.length === 1 ? 'spool' : 'spools' }}\n      </h3>\n\n      <table v-if=\"spoolsAtSelected.length\" class=\"table\">\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>Spool</th>\n            <th>Package</th>\n            <th>Due date</th>\n            <th>Status</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr v-for=\"spool in spoolsAtSelected\" :key=\"spool.id\">\n            <td>{{ spool.spoolNumber }}</td>\n            <td>{{ spool.packageId }}</td>\n            <td>{{ formatDue(spool.dueDate) }}</td>\n            <td>\n              <span v-if=\"spool.isPastDue\" class=\"badge danger\">Past due</span>\n              <span v-else class=\"badge\">On track</span>\n            </td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n\n      <p v-else-if=\"loading\" class=\"muted\">Loading…</p>\n      <p v-else class=\"muted\">No spools are currently at {{ selected }}.</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</template>\n"}}
{"event":"pre-tool-use","timestamp":"2026-06-18T13:59:30.316Z","tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"cd /media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-dashboard-wip-per-station && gh pr create --repo fega/full-stack-engineer-ai-code-challenge --base main --head feat/dashboard-wip-per-station --title \"Dashboard: order WIP per station and separate terminal Installed\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\nImplements the **Dashboard shows WIP per station** task playbook.\n\n- **Backend** (`DashboardService.cs`): `WipByStation` is now an explicitly ordered `IReadOnlyList<WipStationCount>` in domain order (Detailing → Cut → Weld → QC → Shipped → Installed) instead of a `Dictionary<string,int>` whose order was only an incidental serialization artifact. All six stations are emitted including zero counts; since each spool has exactly one `CurrentStation`, the counts partition the spool set and sum to the total.\n- **Installed decision**: `Installed` is the terminal station (no `Next()`), so it is **kept in the API payload** (counts still sum to the total) but **visually separated** in the UI from in-flight WIP.\n- **Frontend** (`App.vue`): updated `DashboardDto` to the array shape; in-flight stations (Detailing → Shipped) render in a legible table with right-aligned tabular counts and an \"In progress\" subtotal; Installed and Past due shown separately below.\n- **Tests** (`DashboardServiceTests.cs`): 3 new tests pinning ordering, per-station counts (incl. zero-count stations and sum-to-total), and empty-repo behaviour.\n\n## Verification\n- `dotnet test` → 5 passed (2 pre-existing + 3 new).\n- `GET /api/dashboard` against seed data returns the ordered array with counts 29/27/23/27/36/58 summing to 200 total spools.\n- `npm run build` succeeds.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":120000,"description":"Create PR against fega repo"}}
