{"event":"pre-tool-use","timestamp":"2026-06-18T14:01:25.899Z","tool_name":"Agent","tool_input":{"description":"Review advance-spool PR","prompt":"Review the code changes on PR #1 of the Stratus Fab Tracker repo. Work in the git worktree at:\n\n/media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-advance-spool-to-next-station-api\n\nThe branch is `feat/advance-spool-to-next-station-api`, base is `main`. Get the full diff with:\n\n    cd /media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-advance-spool-to-next-station-api && git diff main...HEAD\n\nScope of the change (a .NET 8 minimal API + xUnit tests):\n- `src/StratusFabTracker.Api/Application/SpoolWorkflowService.cs` — `AdvanceAsync` now returns `AdvanceOutcome(TransitionResult, Station? NewStation)`.\n- `src/StratusFabTracker.Api/Program.cs` — `POST /api/spools/{id}/advance` now returns `200 OK` with `{ id, currentStation }` (was `204`).\n- New tests: `src/StratusFabTracker.Tests/SpoolWorkflowServiceTests.cs`, `AdvanceEndpointTests.cs`, `TestDoubles.cs`, plus `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing` added to the test csproj.\n\nPlease review for:\n1. Correctness bugs and edge cases in the production code (the advance logic and the new response contract).\n2. Test quality: do the tests actually verify the claims? Any flakiness, shared-state issues across xUnit fixtures, non-deterministic clock usage, or false-confidence assertions? Note the `FakeClock` is intentionally monotonic and a known tie-break defect in `Spool.CurrentStation` is deliberately OUT OF SCOPE (handed off to another task) — do not flag that as a defect to fix here, but DO flag if any test would silently break because of it.\n3. API contract concerns: status codes, response shape, enum serialization (the GET endpoint serializes `Station` as a number by default — is that consistent/intended?).\n4. Anything that would not survive a senior review: naming, error handling, DI lifetime issues (services are singletons), thread-safety of the in-memory repo under the test server.\n\nRun `cd /media/fabian/bigcow/projects/asa/wt-advance-spool-to-next-station-api && dotnet test 2>&1 | tail -15` to confirm the suite passes, and note the result.\n\nReturn a concise findings list, each tagged severity CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW, with file:line and a concrete suggested fix. If you find nothing material, say so explicitly. Do NOT edit any files — review only.","subagent_type":"gsd-code-reviewer"}}
